1. Functional operationalization of the Strategic Support Unit
3. Long-Term Strategy reflected in the Tenth Development Plan;
3. Mathematical models expanded to accommodate sectoral strategies and policies

- Developing new computerised tool and methods for improved radio monitoring, including formulating new set of technical specifications for procurement of modern fully automated Spectrum Management System;
- developing implementation concept and methods for effective geolocation of unauthorised users of radio spectrum, including the use of Unmanned Areal Vehicles for geolocation of satellite communication terminals;
- aiding development of WiMAX (IEEE802.16e) broadband wireless data communication networks throughout the Kingdom, especially in remote border areas, through formulation of methods and procedures for cross-border coordination of radio spectrum use;
- aiding development of public mobile cellular technologies: LTE, LTE-Advanced and introduction of new 1 Gbps-level broadband 5G systems through efficient allocation of necessary spectrum while ensuring their Electromagnetic Compatibility and coordination;
- promoting Private Mobile Radio networks in VHF/UHF bands used by both civil and defence users, through assisting coordination of their use and resolving interference issues with neighbouring countries.
